🧹 1. Sync Local Repo with Remote
Reset local branch to match remote exactly

bash
git fetch origin
git reset --hard origin/main
fetch → gets latest changes

reset --hard → wipes your local changes and matches remote

Use when: local repo is messed up, want clean state

Examples:

You broke your code → just reset to remote

Merge conflicts everywhere → nuke local and sync fresh

❌ 2. Remove File from Git Tracking (Keep Locally)
Remove .env from Git

bash
git rm --cached backend/.env
Stops tracking the file but doesn't delete it from your system

Important: Add to .gitignore after this

Examples:

Accidentally committed secrets

Want .env to stay local only

⏪ 3. Undo Commits
Remove last commit completely

bash
git reset --hard HEAD~1
Deletes last commit + changes (permanently)

Push rewritten history (DANGEROUS)

bash
git push origin main --force
Overwrites remote history with your local version

Reality check: If others work on branch, this wrecks their work

🌿 4. Branch Management
Create and switch to branch from remote

bash
git switch -c master origin/master
Delete remote branch

bash
git push origin --delete branch_name
🔄 5. Pull with Rebase
Rebase local changes on top of remote

bash
git pull --rebase origin develop
Pulls latest develop, re-applies your commits on top (clean history)

🚀 6. Stash Changes (Save Work Temporarily)
Save uncommitted changes

bash
git stash push -m "WIP: fixing login"
Apply latest stash

bash
git stash pop
List stashes

bash
git stash list
Use when: Need to switch branches but have uncommitted work

📝 7. Amend Last Commit
Fix commit message

bash
git commit --amend -m "Better message"
Add forgotten files to last commit

bash
git add forgotten-file.js
git commit --amend --no-edit
Use when: Typo in message or forgot a file

🔍 8. View Commit History
Pretty log with graph

bash
git log --oneline --graph --all
Last 5 commits

bash
git log --oneline -5
Changes in last commit

bash
git show HEAD
🗑️ 9. Clean Working Directory
Remove untracked files

bash
git clean -fd
-f force, -d directories

Remove untracked + ignored files

bash
git clean -fdx
Dry run first:

bash
git clean -n
🔗 10. Remote Management
Add new remote

bash
git remote add upstream https://github.com/other/repo.git
Change remote URL

bash
git remote set-url origin https://github.com/new-owner/repo.git
View remotes

bash
git remote -v
⚡ 11. Cherry-pick Specific Commit
Apply one commit from another branch

bash
git cherry-pick abc1234
Use when: Need one specific fix from main branch

🔄 12. Interactive Rebase (Rewrite History)
Edit last 3 commits

bash
git rebase -i HEAD~3
Squash, reorder, edit, delete commits

DANGEROUS if already pushed

📊 Status Check Commands
bash
git status                    # Current state
git diff                      # Uncommitted changes
git diff --cached             # Staged changes
git log --oneline --graph     # Visual history
git branch -vv                # All branches + tracking
⚠️ Brutal Reality (Don't Ignore)
Destructive commands you're now wielding:

reset --hard → permanent local destruction

push --force → overwrites remote history

rebase -i → rewrites commit history

